  - Where a member of staff is unable to work the contractually agreed
  hours, or is unable to attend a disciplinary or underperformance
  hearing, or the illness/accident occurs during annual leave, or
  uncertified absences exceed ten working days in a year (ECB Staff
  Rules, p.105).   - Any extension of sick leave requires submission
  of a medical certificate; members of staff must inform their
  immediate manager without delay if sick leave is extended (ECB Staff
  Rules, p.106).   - The ECB’s Medical Adviser may at any time require
  a medical certificate for absences and may request information from
  the member’s doctor (ECB Staff Rules, p.106).    Requirements for
  the medical certificate and its handling: the certificate must state
  the date the sickness commenced and the expected end date; a single
  certificate may cover up to six weeks; it must be sent to the
  Directorate General Human Resources as soon as possible, and if the
  absence is likely to exceed one week the certificate shall be posted
  (ECB Staff Rules, pp.105–106).
